The paper is about learning probabilistic models from relational data, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of logical formulas and the focus on interpretability suggests that the paper could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and knowledge representation (cs.CR). Finally, the use of relational data suggests that the paper could also be relevant to databases (cs.DB).
